This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with communication protocols in IoT systems. It may also belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category as it involves the study of information transmission and coding. Additionally, it could be classified under Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it deals with secure communication in IoT systems. Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) are also possible sub-categories as they involve the study of distributed systems and control in IoT systems.
